records.addlTxt: 1:46 PM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Garrett L Laurence in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court.  Attorney Breanna A. Halyburton in court for Garrett L Laurence. State - here for a PH. State calls Detective Sgt. Darrell Wilson. Wilson sworn in at 1:47 PM. Direct exam by State. Record reflects proper identification of the defendant (1:49 PM). Cross exam by Halyburton at 1:50 PM. Court finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State has filed the Information. Halyburton has the Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts plea, continues bond, set for JT.

records.addlTxt: Adjourned initial appearance on May 18, 2022 at 11:45 am.

10:04 AM Defendant Garrett L Laurence appears by video, in custody from FC jail.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Laurence has not received a copy of the complaint. Court reads charges and penalties. Laurence understands. Court questions if he has contacted an attorney. Laurence has spoken with an attorney. Court will have scheduled for AIA to allow time for Laurence to contact his attorney to review this case. State asks for bond to continue. Laurence asks for signature bond - starting work. Court explains once talks to an attorney can address bond. Court will continue bond at this time.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for May 18, 2022 at 11:45 am.
